-- L&G says bond fund manager Hodges to leave
-- 
-- Tue Apr 22, 2014 11:48AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, April 22 (Reuters) - Legal & General Investment Management's (LGIM) senior bond fund manager Richard Hodges plans to leave the company in October after seven years, the company said on Tuesday.

Hodges has resigned in order to pursue other opportunities and will hand over management of the 2 billion pounds ($3.36 billion) Legal & General Dynamic Bond Trust to colleague Martin Reeves, a spokeswoman said.